parameters.name: EndTime
parameters.description: The end of the time range to query. The value of this parameter must be a timestamp that follows the UNIX time format.

parameters.name: ExecState
parameters.description:
The execution status of the SQL statement. Valid values:

*   **FAIL**: The execution of the SQL statement fails.
*   **CANCEL**: The execution of the SQL statement is canceled.
*   **SUCCESS**: The SQL statement is executed.

parameters.name: PageNumber
parameters.description: The number of the page to return.

parameters.name: PageSize
parameters.description: The number of entries to return on each page. Maximum values: 100.

parameters.name: SQLType
parameters.description:
The type of SQL statement. Valid values:

*   **SELECT**
*   **INSERT**
*   **DELETE**
*   **CREATE_TABLE**

>  You can choose Operation Audit > Secure Access Proxy in the top navigation bar of the DMS console to view more types of SQL statements.

parameters.name: SearchName
parameters.description: The name of the database instance.

parameters.name: StartTime
parameters.description: The beginning of the time range to query. The value of this parameter must be a timestamp that follows the UNIX time format.

parameters.name: Tid
parameters.description: The ID of the tenant. You can call the [GetUserActiveTenant](~~198073~~) operation to query the tenant ID.
